cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a generative sequence model that learns representations containing explicit beliefs about states several steps into the future. The model is trained using temporal difference learning used in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of the model in planning and acting in complex environments, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The model's ability to learn representations of states could also make it relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the model in image prediction, which could make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
